title: Top Global Rank in Control of Corruption
description: In 2023, Norway achieved a perfect score of 100 in the Control of Corruption percentile rank, indicating the highest level of integrity and transparency in governance worldwide.

title: Universal Financial Inclusion for Older Adults
description: As of 2021, 100% of Norwegians aged 25 and above have access to financial institutions or mobile money services, showcasing complete financial inclusion for older adults.

title: Universal Financial Access for Educated Youth
description: In 2021, Norway reported that 100% of individuals aged 15 and above with secondary education or more have access to financial services, highlighting comprehensive financial inclusion among educated youth.

title: Exceptional GNI Per Capita Growth
description: Norway experienced a remarkable 25.02% growth in GNI per capita in 2022, reflecting significant economic expansion and prosperity.

title: Near-Universal Primary School Enrollment
description: In 2017, Norway achieved a net primary school enrollment rate of 99.88%, ensuring almost all children have access to primary education.

title: Low Mortality from Air Pollution Among Males
description: The mortality rate attributed to household and ambient air pollution for males was 9.4 per 100,000 in 2019, one of the lowest globally, indicating effective environmental policies.

title: Minimal Maternal Mortality
description: In 2023, Norway reported a maternal mortality ratio of 1 per 100,000 live births, showcasing one of the safest environments for childbirth globally.

title: High Health Expenditure Per Capita
description: In 2022, Norway's domestic general government health expenditure per capita was $7,447.64, reflecting a strong commitment to public health.

title: High Health Expenditure in PPP Terms
description: Norway's health expenditure per capita in PPP terms was $8,505.55 in 2022, indicating substantial investment in healthcare relative to purchasing power.

title: High Consumption for Bottom 40%
description: In 2022, the bottom 40% of Norway's population had a mean consumption of $49.42 per day, highlighting equitable wealth distribution.

title: Low Bound Rates on Primary Products
description: In 2021, Norway maintained a low bound rate of 0.56% on primary products, promoting trade and economic openness.

title: Top Global Rank in Voice and Accountability
description: Norway achieved a perfect score of 100 in the Voice and Accountability percentile rank in 2023, reflecting a robust democratic environment.

title: High Voice and Accountability Estimate
description: In 2023, Norway's Voice and Accountability estimate was 1.78, showcasing strong democratic governance and citizen participation.

title: High Confidence in Democratic Processes
description: With a lower bound confidence interval of 96.08% in 2023, Norway demonstrates strong confidence in its democratic processes.
